      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Many thanks for the fragments of the two rare plants you sent me, both are known but from other localities ¶ &amp;c &amp;c &amp;c interpolated following a closing quotation mark. ¶ I wish you could induce all int...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">71.12.00d</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="">To L.W.C</seg>
               <seg style=""/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found. The text given here is from </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Herald</seg>
                     <seg style=""> (Fremantle), 23 December 1871, p. 3 (B71.12.09). It is appended to a letter to the Editor from L.W.C. dated 15 December that says: 'I send you extracts from a letter I have just received from Baron Von Mueller, Curator of Botanical Gardens'. <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>L.W.C has not been identified. The letter is dated to early December on the basis that the mail from the eastern colonies arrived in Fremantle early on 14 December 1871 (</seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Herald</seg>
                     <seg style="">, 16 December 1871, p. 3), <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>for <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>which the Melbourne mail for Western Australia closed on 6 December (</seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Argus</seg>
                     <seg style="">, 4 December 1871, p. 4).</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
               <seg style="">Many thanks for the fragments of the two rare plants you sent me, both are known but from other localities</seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                     <p rend="Footnote"
                        style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>&amp;c &amp;c &amp;c </seg>
                        <seg style="font-style: italic; ">interpolated following a closing quotation mark</seg>
                        <seg style="">.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I wish you could induce all intelligent and educated inland settlers to collect the plants of the vicinity and send them to me by parcel post. </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Nothing</seg>
               <seg style=""> will come amiss from your colony, as the </seg>
               <seg style="font-style: italic; ">range</seg>
               <seg style=""> of the </seg>
               <seg style="font-style: italic; ">species</seg>
               <seg style=""> have to be determined. </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The collectors names will always be given in my works. </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Perhaps your local papers would help, and insert a memorandum, drawing attention to my wishes. </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>We want the plants as well in flower as in fruit. </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Would your intelligent children (throughout, the colony?) dry Seaweeds for me, if I spent a few pounds on the subject?</seg>
            </p>
         </div>
